âœ… QUESTION 1 â€” Flow / Synchronization (ArrayList)
ðŸ”¹ Problem (Simplified, Exam Style)

You are given:

N intersections

initial_flow as an ArrayList

A range [L, R]

sync_threshold

Rules:

If all values in [L, R] â‰¥ sync_threshold, system is synchronized.

Effective flow per step = flow[L] * flow[R]

You can pick all intersections once and add the same effective flow.

Find total effective flow.

ðŸ”¹ Input
N = 3
initial_flow = [5, 5, 5]
L = 0, R = 2
sync_threshold = 0

ðŸ§  Logic

Check synchronization

Compute effective flow once

Add it N times

âœ… Java Code (ArrayList)
import java.util.*;

public class FlowSynchronization {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ArrayList<Integer> flow = new ArrayList<>();
        flow.add(5);
        flow.add(5);
        flow.add(5);

        int L = 0, R = 2;
        int syncThreshold = 0;

        boolean synchronizedFlow = true;
        for (int i = L; i <= R; i++) {
            if (flow.get(i) < syncThreshold) {
                synchronizedFlow = false;
                break;
            }
        }

        int total = 0;
        if (synchronizedFlow) {
            int effective = flow.get(L) * flow.get(R);
            for (int i = 0; i < flow.size(); i++) {
                total += effective;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(total);
    }
}

âœ… Output
75
